ure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131977118,imgsize-189262.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indonesian proverb of the day: 'An elephant at the edge of the eye is not seen, but an ant across the ocean is seen']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131976121.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[This ancient Indonesian proverb, 'An elephant at the edge of one’s own eye goes unnoticed, while an ant across the ocean is clearly seen,' captures the essence of our inclination to criticize minor issues in others while overlooking our own significant shortcomings. With deep roots in oral tradition, it aligns with contemporary psychology regarding cognitive bias.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indonesian-proverb-of-the-day-an-elephant-at-the-edge-of-the-eye-is-not-seen-but-an-ant-across-the-ocean-is-seen-why-we-notice-others-faults-more-than-our-own/articleshow/131976121.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indonesian-proverb-of-the-day-an-elephant-at-the-edge-of-the-eye-is-not-seen-but-an-ant-across-the-ocean-is-seen-why-we-notice-others-faults-more-than-our-own/articleshow/131976121.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-25T00:30:45+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131976388,imgsize-137672.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mongolian proverb of the day: 'Suffer with your own rule, rather than frolic under someone else’s rule']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131975817.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In Mongolia, a saying goes, 'Suffer with your own rule, rather than frolic under someone else’s rule.' This wisdom reflects a strong cultural belief in self-sufficiency over ease. Born from the expansive steppes and their nomadic lifestyle, the phrase underscores the importance of personal freedom and decision-making, even if those choices come with challenges. It’s a timeless reminder that true integrity stems from self-determination.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/mongolian-proverb-of-the-day-suffer-with-your-own-rule-rather-than-frolic-under-someone-elses-rule-a-lesson-in-freedom-from-the-land-of-genghis-khan/articleshow/131975817.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/mongolian-proverb-of-the-day-suffer-with-your-own-rule-rather-than-frolic-under-someone-elses-rule-a-lesson-in-freedom-from-the-land-of-genghis-khan/articleshow/131975817.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-25T00:10:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131976048,imgsize-188904.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistani man held French woman, children captive for 12 years; child's escape leads to rescue]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131972993.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistani-man-held-french-woman-children-captive-for-12-years-childs-escape-leads-to-rescue/articleshow/131972993.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistani-man-held-french-woman-children-captive-for-12-years-childs-escape-leads-to-rescue/articleshow/131972993.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T23:56:07+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131975590,imgsize-60918.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[French mother, 5 children rescued from Pak home after decade-long captivity]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131974019.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A French mother and her five children have been dramatically rescued from a decade of alleged captivity and abuse in Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. Sylvie Yasmina, who claims her husband 'effectively imprisoned' them after moving from Australia in 2014, was found with visible injuries. Her son's brave escape to a police station led to the family's liberation and her expressed desire to return to France.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/french-mother-five-children-rescued-from-pakistan-home-after-decade-long-captivity-abuse-by-husband/articleshow/131974019.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/french-mother-five-children-rescued-from-pakistan-home-after-decade-long-captivity-abuse-by-husband/articleshow/131974019.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T23:07:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131974197,imgsize-91164.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bipartisan housing bill left unsigned as Trump prioritises 'SAVE America Act']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131972732.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/bipartisan-housing-bill-left-unsigned-as-trump-prioritises-save-america-act/articleshow/131972732.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/bipartisan-housing-bill-left-unsigned-as-trump-prioritises-save-america-act/articleshow/131972732.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T22:09:48+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131973032,imgsize-51444.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meet Aashna Doshi, Indian-origin Google engineer who quit her dream job at 23 to build...]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131972306.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-aashna-doshi-indian-origin-google-engineer-who-quit-her-dream-job-at-23-to-build-a-podcast-and-ai-startup/articleshow/131972306.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-aashna-doshi-indian-origin-google-engineer-who-quit-her-dream-job-at-23-to-build-a-podcast-and-ai-startup/articleshow/131972306.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T22:01:53+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131972326,imgsize-147122.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bill Gates says Jeffrey Epstein sought to blackmail him over extramarital affairs]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131972117.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Bill Gates revealed to US lawmakers that Jeffrey Epstein appeared to be contemplating blackmail over his extramarital affairs, citing "veiled" threats and draft emails. Gates, testifying before the House Oversight Committee, stated he was never blackmailed but acknowledged Epstein explored using personal information to maintain influence. He expressed regret over his association with the late sex offender, calling it a "grave error in judgment."]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/bill-gates-says-jeffrey-epstein-sought-to-blackmail-him-over-extramarital-affairs/articleshow/131972117.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/bill-gates-says-jeffrey-epstein-sought-to-blackmail-him-over-extramarital-affairs/articleshow/131972117.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T21:32:20+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131972406,imgsize-1106950.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Who is Vinod Doddamani? Indian-origin attorney in US faces $250,000 fine over fraud claims]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131970897.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/who-is-vinod-doddamani-indian-origin-immigration-attorney-in-us-faces-250000-fine-over-fraud-claims-involving-indian-nationals/articleshow/131970897.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/who-is-vinod-doddamani-indian-origin-immigration-attorney-in-us-faces-250000-fine-over-fraud-claims-involving-indian-nationals/articleshow/131970897.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T20:33:37+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131971564,imgsize-118302.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Henry Nowak murder: Police took 8 minutes to find stab wound after being misled by Vickrum Digwa ]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131971305.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/henry-nowak-murder-police-took-8-minutes-to-find-stab-wound-after-sikh-man-vickrum-digwas-false-racist-attack-claim/articleshow/131971305.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/henry-nowak-murder-police-took-8-minutes-to-find-stab-wound-after-sikh-man-vickrum-digwas-false-racist-attack-claim/articleshow/131971305.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T20:22:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131971508,imgsize-66238.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UAE Central Bank fines foreign bank branch AED20 million over anti-money laundering failures]]></title><description><![CDATA[A foreign bank's UAE branch has been hit with a hefty AED20 million fine by the Central Bank of the UAE. This action stems from serious and recurring lapses in the bank's anti-money laundering and counter-terrorist financing systems.  The bank's Head of Compliance also faces a AED300,000 penalty for failing to meet their duties, underscoring the regulator's commitment to financial system integrity.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-central-bank-fines-foreign-bank-branch-aed20-million-over-anti-money-laundering-failures/articleshow/131971344.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-central-bank-fines-foreign-bank-branch-aed20-million-over-anti-money-laundering-failures/articleshow/131971344.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T20:17:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131971483,imgsize-467126.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Suffered a heatstroke’: Italy rebuts Nato chief's claim on US flights supporting Iran strikes]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131971185.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Italy has refuted Nato chief Mark Rutte's claim that hundreds of US aircraft flew from Italian bases for operations against Iran. Rome insists only technical and logistical support was authorized, not combat missions. This clarification follows Rutte's remarks to Fox News, which sparked political backlash in Italy. The government maintains its actions align with constitutional and treaty obligations, refusing requests beyond approved limits.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/suffered-a-heatstroke-italy-rebuts-nato-chief-ruttes-claim-on-us-flights-supporting-iran-strikes/articleshow/131971185.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/suffered-a-heatstroke-italy-rebuts-nato-chief-ruttes-claim-on-us-flights-supporting-iran-strikes/articleshow/131971185.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T20:15:48+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131971390,imgsize-678120.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How an Indian woman confronted Bangladeshi waiter for making anti-India remarks in viral video]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131969316.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/say-sorry-how-an-indian-woman-confronted-bangladeshi-waiter-for-making-anti-india-remarks-in-italy-in-viral-video/articleshow/131969316.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/say-sorry-how-an-indian-woman-confronted-bangladeshi-waiter-for-making-anti-india-remarks-in-italy-in-viral-video/articleshow/131969316.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-24T19:37:31+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure 